<ext_description linkend="Cost_schedule_arm.Cost_schedule">
        A <b>Cost_schedule</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="root_things:arm:Root_things_arm.Information_object" />
that records or predicts costs within an AEC project.

<note number="1">A <b>Cost_schedule</b> can apply to a complete project, to a section of a project, or to an item within a project.
</note>

<note number="2">One <b>Cost_schedule</b> can have another <b>Cost_schedule</b> as a part.
</note>

A <b>Cost_schedule</b> ultimately applies to an activity.  When the <express_ref linkend="cost_schedule:arm:Cost_schedule_arm.Cost_schedule.costed_item"/> for a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is an 
<express_ref linkend="root_things:arm:Root_things_arm.Information_object"/> or 
<express_ref linkend="aec_functions_and_domains:arm:Aec_functions_and_domains_arm.Aec_physical_object"/>, there is an activity associated with the object to which the <b>Cost_schedule</b> applies.

<note number="3">
<p>When a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is assigned to an <express_ref linkend="root_things:arm:Root_things_arm.Information_object"/> that is a report, the activity to which the <b>Cost_schedule</b> applies often consists of:</p>
<ul>
<li>writing the report;</li>
<li>delivering the report to the customer;</li>
<li>assigning the intellectual property rights to the customer.</li>
</ul>
</note>



<note number="4">
<p>When a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is assigned to an 
<express_ref linkend="aec_functions_and_domains:arm:Aec_functions_and_domains_arm.Aec_material_asset"/>, 
the activity to which the <b>Cost_schedule</b> applies often consists of:</p>
<ul>
 	<li>procuring the material asset;</li>
 	<li>delivering material asset to the customers site;</li>
 	<li>assigning ownership of the material asset to the customer.</li>
</ul>
</note>

The cost for a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is ultimately an activity.  When the cost for a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is a <express_ref linkend="currency:arm:Currency_arm.Currency_value"/>, 
there is a payment activity associated with the amount to which the <b>Cost_schedule</b> applies.

<note number="5">
<p>When a <b>Cost_schedule</b> is assigned to a 
<express_ref linkend="currency:arm:Currency_arm.Currency_value"/>, the activity to which the <b>Cost_schedule</b> applies is often defined by:</p>
<ul>
<li>the amount to be paid;</li>
<li>the account into which it is to be paid;</li>
<li>the date of payment.</li>
</ul>
</note>

<note number="6">The cost for a <b>Cost_schedule</b> can be a activity which is not the payment of a <express_ref linkend="currency:arm:Currency_arm.Currency_value"/>. 
The activity can be a transfer of ownership of assets such as shares.
</note>

</ext_description>
